in using optimal alpha, we set a threshold that will minimize the probability of making a mistake when we choose to accept or reject the null. <br>
<img src = \"data:image/png;base64,\" class=\"myimages\"><br>Figure 2: Determination of optimal α from the a priori combined probabilities of Type I and II error.  Α and ω for independent 2-tailed, 2 sample t-tests (n1 = n2).  Data are for 3 (dotted line). 10 (solid line) and 30 (double line) samples per group, with critical effects sizes of 1 σ where, ω = (α + β)/2 (i.e.  average of Type I and Type II error).  Drop lines indicate the minimum ω and its associated value for α. <br></p3>
